'''弓鳍鱼'''（[[學名|學名]]：{{lang|la|''Amia calva''}}）是[[弓鳍鱼目|弓鳍鱼目]][[弓鳍鱼科|弓鳍鱼科]][[弓鳍鱼属|弓鳍鱼属]]目前仅存的一种，属于[[全骨下纲|全骨下纲]]的[[辐鳍鱼|辐鳍鱼类]]，与[[雀鳝目|雀鳝目]]的亲缘关系较近，也是一种[[活化石|活化石]]。从[[侏罗纪|侏罗纪]]的化石中就有弓鳍鱼類存在，但目前只剩本種生存在[[密西西比河|密西西比河]]流域和[[北美洲|北美洲]]东部的河流、湖泊中。体长可达一米，性凶猛，以动物性食物为主。

==特征==

[[File:AmiaCalvaHeadLankester.jpg|thumb]]

身体延长，稍侧扁，雌魚長{{convert|65|-|70|cm|in|abbr=on}}，雄魚長{{convert|50|-|65|cm|in|abbr=on}}。其最長可達{{convert|109|cm|in|abbr=on}}，重{{convert|9.75|kg|lb|abbr=on}}<ref name="FB">{{FishBase family|family=Amiidae|year=2009|month=January}}</ref>。新生的弓鰭魚在一年內就可以長到{{convert|13|-|23|cm|in|abbr=on}}。<ref name="FLMNH">{{cite web | url=http://www.flmnh.ufl.edu/fish/Gallery/Descript/Bowfin/Bowfin.html | title=Bowfin | publisher=Florida Museum of Natural History | work=Ichthyology at the Florida Museum of Natural History | accessdate=June 11, 2014 | author=University of Florida | archive-date=2016-01-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160104214933/https://www.flmnh.ufl.edu/fish/Gallery/Descript/Bowfin/Bowfin.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

体被有革狀硬鱗，颏部有一喉板；背鳍延长，臀鳍短；尾部近似正尾形，后缘为圆形，尾部靠背处有一大黑斑，雄性尾鳍上也有一个外黄内黑的斑点，背鳍延长，鳔大，有[[红血球|红血球]]，在缺氧时可以临时用[[鳔|鳔]]呼吸。颌部有喉板，尾鳍近乎正圆形。

==生態==
本魚棲息於植物茂盛的湖泊或溪流中，屬肉食性，以[[魚類|魚類]]、[[青蛙|青蛙]]、[[甲殼類|甲殼類]]、[[蠕蟲|蠕蟲]]等為食，繁殖期約在每年4至7月，雄魚會在淺灘以水草築巢，並建立勢力範圍，雌魚每次產卵數為3萬顆，卵約8至10天孵化。

==經濟利用==

它被釣魚愛好者所青睞，但是其攻擊性很強，牙齒鋒利，因此需要格外小心處理。<ref name=NYS>{{cite web|url=http://www.dec.ny.gov/animals/77506.html|title=The Bowfin, New York's Disrespected Living Fossil|publisher=New York Department of Environmental Conservation|author=Randy Jackson|accessdate=June 4, 2014|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427195817/https://www.dec.ny.gov/animals/77506.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="StewartWatkinson2004"/><ref name="igfa">{{cite web|url=http://www.igfa.org/species/100-bowfin.aspx?CommonName=100-bowfin.aspx|title=Bowfin|publisher=International Game Fish Association|author=IGFA|accessdate=June 4, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181012140152/https://www.igfa.org/species/100-bowfin.aspx?CommonName=100-bowfin.aspx|archive-date=2018-10-12|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

它的肉口感並不好<ref name="StewartWatkinson2004">{{cite book|author1=Kenneth Stewart|author2=Douglas Watkinson|title=Freshwater Fish of Manitoba|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VyzuWkePgtsC&pg=PA51|date=3 May 2004|publisher=Univ. of Manitoba Press|isbn=978-0-88755-374-5|page=51}}</ref><ref name="Schultz2010">{{cite book|author=Ken Schultz|title=Ken Schultz's Field Guide to Freshwater Fish|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jXkW9mYqP8oC&pg=PA64|date=15 December 2010|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-1-118-03987-8|page=64}}</ref>，但在熏製或烹飪之後仍可食用<ref name="StewartWatkinson2004"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailycomet.com/article/20090405/ARTICLES/904039977?p=2&tc=pg|publisher=Daily Comet|title=Choupique may be a trash fish for some, treasure to others|author=David A. Bourgeois|date=April 5, 2009|access-date=2020-04-01|archive-date=2016-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160314055743/http://www.dailycomet.com/article/20090405/ARTICLES/904039977?p=2&tc=pg|dead-url=no}}</ref>。它的魚籽有時候會被當做[[鱘魚子|鱘魚子]]的替代品<ref name=NYTimes>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/06/10/us/scarcity-of-beluga-caviar-opens-the-door-for-louisiana.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0|newspaper=New York Times|title=A Roe, By Any Other Name|author=Susan Saulny|date=June 9, 2012|accessdate=2020-04-01|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427051314/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/06/10/us/scarcity-of-beluga-caviar-opens-the-door-for-louisiana.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>，商品名為“Cajun caviar”、“Choupiquet Royale”。<ref name=Nicholls>{{cite web|url=http://www.nicholls.edu/bayousphere/GraduateStudents/JDavis/Davis_Thesis.pdf|publisher=Nicholls State University|title=Reproductive Biology, Life History and Population Structure of a Bowfin ''Amia calva'' Population in Southeastern Louisiana, Fall 2003|author=Johnathan G. Davis|accessdate=June 7, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818182402/https://www.nicholls.edu/bayousphere/GraduateStudents/JDavis/Davis_Thesis.pdf|archive-date=2016-08-18|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fws.gov/eddies/episodeSpring2013/american_fishes/index.html|publisher=USF&WS|title=Bowfin: North America's Freshwater Thug|author=Christopher Scharpf|date=December 30, 2013|access-date=2020-04-01|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427155720/https://www.fws.gov/eddies/episodeSpring2013/american_fishes/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

